---
layout: base.njk
title: Web Everything - Semantics
---
{% from "we-component.njk" import weCard %}

<div class="container">
    <div class="block-header">
        <a href="/" class="back-link">&larr; Back Home</a>
        <h1 class="block-title">Semantics & Glossary</h1>
        <p class="lead">Ubiquitous language and precise definitions to remove ambiguity from the Web Everything protocols.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="content">

        {# Alpha Index #}
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-24 justify-center w-full">
            {% for item in semantics %}
                <a href="#term-{{ item.term | slugify }}" 
                   class="px-3 py-1 text-sm font-code text-slate-600 hover:text-indigo-600 hover:bg-white rounded transition-colors break-words"
                   title="{{ item.definition }}">
                    {{ item.term }}
                </a>
            {% endfor %}
        </div>

        {#- Proof-of-life for the generic SSR card primitive (#2098): the glossary's single section-card is
            authored via the `weCard` macro instead of a hand-rolled `.section-card fui-card`. The macro emits
            an inert `<we-card data-we-spec>` placeholder that the `weComponentSSR` build transform batches
            through the pinned FUI CLI (one subprocess for the page) and splices to the finished SSR
            `<article class="fui-card">` — byte-identical to the client `<we-card>` CE upgrade, JS-off correct.
            The `.p-0.overflow-hidden` chrome the prior frame carried moves onto the card via `className`. -#}
        {%- set _semanticsBody %}
            {% for item in semantics %}
            <div id="term-{{ item.term | slugify }}" class="semantic-item p-6 border-b border-slate-200 scroll-mt-24 target:bg-indigo-50 transition-colors">
                <div class="flex flex-wrap items-baseline gap-3 mb-2">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-mono font-bold text-slate-900 break-words">{{ item.term }}</h3>
                    <a href="#term-{{ item.term | slugify }}" class="text-slate-300 hover:text-indigo-400">#</a>
                </div>
                <p class="text-slate-800 mb-3 text-lg leading-relaxed break-words">{{ item.definition }}</p>
                {% if item.usage %}
                <div class="bg-slate-50 p-3 rounded text-sm text-slate-600 border border-slate-100 overflow-x-auto">
                    <span class="font-bold text-slate-500 block uppercase text-xs mb-1 tracking-wider">Context & Usage</span>
                    <span class="break-words">{{ item.usage | safe }}</span>
                </div>
                {% endif %}
            </div>
            {% endfor %}
        {% endset -%}
        {{ weCard("", _semanticsBody, "", "section-card p-0 overflow-hidden") }}
    </div>
</div>
